article.headline: Penn State 69, North Carolina Greensboro 56
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Jamelle Cornley scored 23 points and pulled down 11 rebounds, and Ben Luber added 13 points as Penn State beat UNC-Greensboro 69-56 Monday night. Penn State built an eight-point lead midway through the second half, but the Spartans rallied to tie after a pair of 3-pointers and a layup from Kyle Hines. But Hines, who finished with 20 points and seven rebounds, picked up his fourth foul with 9:09 left, and UNC-Greensboro didn't hit a field goal for more than four minutes. Penn State responded by going on an 18-4 run that put the game out of reach, highlighted by a Luber 3-pointer off a pretty behind-the-back pass by Mike Walker and a D.J. Jackson putback. Bart Tooms added 12 points on 5-of-6 shooting off the bench for the Spartans. Both teams looked to pound the ball inside early, and Cornley and center Brandon Hassell carried the load for Penn State. Cornley finished the first half with eight points and two rebounds, while Hassell scored seven, including two on a dunk over Hines. Hassell finished the game with nine points and five rebounds.
